	(197,3,'2014-08-05 08:35:34','2014-08-05 08:35:34','<span style=\"color: #333333;\">This site was generously designed and developed by Matthew and Arlene Santos, Owners of AG Design Group, Inc., an award winning, full service Creative Marketing and Project Management Consultancy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\">Matt and Arlene’s involvement with the Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco started with a Family Meal they volunteer for in 2003 as college students at USF.  They continued to support the House over the years by Naming the House in their United Way campaign and company matching gift program, and more in recent years as Gold or Platinum Gala Sponsors.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\">In 2013 they offered to further support the House by offering an in-kind donation of a full, end-to-end, website redesign and development of the Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco’s website featuring:</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\"> -   A new, up-to-date look and better user information flow</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\"> -   Easy to use content management system</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\"> -   Social Media and Rich Media features and integration</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\"> -   A Mobile Optimized website that is accessible from various mobile devices</span>\r\n\r\n“The website has been a labor of love. Our job was to re-design the Frontend with adherence to the Ronald McDonald House brand guidelines, re-architect the functionality, and translate this over to mobile.  We re-engineer the flow, layout and experience of the site, in order to bring the website to life. Our hope is that the new website brings more traffic and attention to the House’s cause, increases donor response, and is a launching pad for charity events and all the great work and services the House and it’s staff provides.”\r\n- Arlene Santos, CEO of AG Design Group.\r\n\r\n“In order to make the website truly usable, users need t