	(336,5,'2014-11-22 01:13:24','2014-11-22 01:13:24','<h2 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Referrals &amp; Admission</strong></h2>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Requests for rooms at the Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco are made through the Department of Social Work at the hospital where the patient is receiving treatment. Due to the large number of referrals, we prioritize based on level of care, projected length of stay and distance from San Francisco. Unfortunately, a request does not guarantee availability of rooms.</p>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The following requirements must be met to stay at the Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco.</p>\n\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\n	<li>The patient must be 18 years or younger and receiving treatment in a San Francisco hospital.</li>\n	<li>The child’s permanent address must be at least 50 miles from San Francisco.</li>\n	<li>Adults staying in the House must have current, valid photo identification.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Returning Families</strong><strong> </strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Returning families may call to verify availability and put their names on the waiting list.  Confirmation with the Department of Social Work at the hospital where the patient is receiving treatment will still be necessary.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Hours</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The House is accessible to families 24 hours a day, 365 days a year.</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Registration Hours:</strong></h4>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Monday – Friday:  2 p.m. – 8 p.m. Saturday:  8 a.m. – 11 a.m. Sunday:  6 p.m. – 8 p.m.</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Office Hours:</strong></h4>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Monday - Friday:  9 a.m. – 9 p.m. Saturday:  8 a.m. – noon Sunday:  5 p.m. – 9 p.m.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Check In</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Your check in time must be confirmed with the Ronald McDonald House. Failure to arrive or inform staff that you will be late will result in another family being placed in the House.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Children</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Indoor and outdoor play spaces are available for our young guests.  Parents are required to be responsible for their own children and provide supervision at all times. Children under 18 may not be left unattended. Parents are also asked to clean up after their children in the playroom, dining room and common areas. The House does not provide baby-sitting services.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Family Chores</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Families are asked to assist with small household chores around the House. All guests are responsible for keeping their rooms tidy and washing their own linens as needed.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Security</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">For security, the House doors are locked at all times and guests are given keys. Please note: we cannot be responsible for any accidents, thefts, or losses incurred by guests while staying at the House.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Restrictions</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Smoking is not allowed in the House and is restricted to designated areas.  Pets, firearms, alcohol and illegal drugs are not permitted on RMH-SF property.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Charges</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">In order to offset some of the costs, we ask families to contribute $10 per night, per room.  However, if this presents a hardship, arrangements can be made with the Program Director.</p>\n\n<h2 style=\"color: #227896;\">Helpful Resources</h2>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>DISCLAIMER: The resources &amp; organizations listed below are not programs of the Ronald McDonald House nor do they represent RMH-SF in any capacity. This list only serves to provide guests with local resources that may provide additional services other than those offered by RMH-SF.</em></p>\n\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Transportation</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The UCSF Medical Center operates <a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.campuslifeservices.ucsf.edu/transportation/shuttles/\" target=\"_blank\">free shuttle services</a> between the Ronald McDonald House and the UCSF Parnassus campus Monday-Friday, between 7 a.m. – 8 p.m. (excluding campus holidays). No eating, drinking or smoking is permitted in the shuttle vehicle. For more information, guests can call the shuttle hotline between 8 a.m. – 5 p.m. at 415.476.4646.</p>\n\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\n	<li>The California Pacific Medical Center is a short MUNI bus ride away using the #2 or #4 bus lines.</li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.bart.gov/\" target=\"_blank\">Bay Area Rapid Transit</a> (BART)</li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.sfmta.com/cms/home/sfmta.php\" target=\"_blank\">Municipal Transportation Agency</a> (MUNI)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Helpful Links</strong></h3>\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.aap.org/\" target=\"_blank\">American Academy of Pediatrics</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.cpmc.org/\" target=\"_blank\">California Pacific Medical Center</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.carepages.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Care Pages</a> – Free Patient Blogs</li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"ronaldhouse-sf.org\" target=\"_blank\">Helping Children After a Disaster</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://healthy.kaiserpermanente.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Kaiser Permanente</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.sfdph.org/dph/comupg/oservices/medsvs/sfgh/\" target=\"_blank\">San Francisco General Hospital &amp; Trauma Center</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"https://www.starbrightworld.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Starbright World</a> – Social network for teens with life-threatening medical conditions</li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.ucsfhealth.org/\" target=\"_blank\">UCSF Medical Center</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 style=\"color: #227896;\"><strong>Grief / Bereavement</strong></h3>\n<ul style=\"color: #000000;\">\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.compassionatefriends.org/home.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Compassionate Friends</a></li>\n	<li><a style=\"color: #780005;\" href=\"http://www.dougy.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Dougy Center</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>* Some of the listed resources were compiled by the Child Life Council.</em></p>','Guest Resources','','inherit','open','open','','156-autosave-v1','','','2014-11-22 01:13:24','2014-11-22 01:13:24','',156,'http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/156-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
