	(382,4,'2014-12-09 12:05:56','2014-12-09 20:05:56','<h2><a href=\"http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/MG_6554.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-296\" src=\"http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/MG_6554-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"_MG_6554\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a></h2>\r\n<h2>Annual Patrick Marleau Golf Tournament raises nearly $250,000 for new House at Mission Bay and Scott Street renovations</h2>\r\n<em>August 2014 -</em> Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco’s annual Patrick Marleau Golf Classic took place on August 25th and was a great success! With Patrick’s and our sponsors’ help, we were able to raise nearly $250,000 toward our Hearts &amp; Hands Campaign. Approximately 130 golfers teed off Monday morning and completed their round by the late afternoon. Immediately following the tournament, Dave Clark, anchorman for KTVU Channel 2 Morning News, hosted a reception which included silent and live auctions.\r\n\r\nThe House relies on this annual fundraiser for nearly 15% of our revenue. The funds raised will go toward renovating our flagship Scott Street House, and opening the new House inside UCSF Benioff Children’s Hospital at Mission Bay. With the added capacity, RMH-SF will be able to nearly triple the number of families we currently serve.','2014 Patrick Marleau Golf Classic','','inherit','open','open','','233-revision-v1','','','2014-12-09 12:05:56','2014-12-09 20:05:56','',233,'http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/233-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(383,4,'2014-12-09 14:44:02','2014-12-09 22:44:02','<a href=\"http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/WB-High5c.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-384\" src=\"http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/WB-High5c-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"WB High5c\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\n\n<em>October 30, 2014</em> - The House hosted its annual Home Away From Home gala on October 17th at the Four Seasons in San Francisco and, through the generosity of new and longtime supporters, was able to raise nearly $325,000–exceeding goals for the event and setting a new fundraising record for the House. Of the funds raised, $86,000 came from the Fill-A-Heart individual donation portion of the live auction.\n\nAnother first for the House was achieved when Senator Mark Leno presented a resolution to honor the House’s 25 years of service to families with critically ill children. Masters of Ceremony Cheryl Jennings and Mike Nicco added a lively energy to the program and highlighted personal stories from families who have stayed at the House. The evening ended with dinner and a dance floor jam-packed thanks to music by the ever-popular Pride &amp; Joy.\n\n&nbsp;','Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco Hosts 25th Anniversary Gala; Exceeds Fundraising Goals','','inherit','open','open','','1-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-09 14:44:02','2014-12-09 22:44:02','',1,'http://ronaldhouse-sf.org.97.69-195-223.groveurl.com/1-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
